#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:247
#, no-c-format
msgid "PowerDevil Runner"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PowerDevil can be manually controlled through &krunner; (<keycombo "
"action=\"simul\">&Alt;<keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>"
"). This makes changing profile, brightness, governor and more much easier and "
"faster. The runner has various keywords you can enter to access its functions"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:252
#, no-c-format
msgid "Runner Keywords"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:253
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here comes a list of keywords you can enter in &krunner; to perform PowerDevil "
"related actions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid "Power Profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can manually choose a profile using this keyword. All available profiles "
"will be shown in form of &krunner; matches."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:273
#, no-c-format
msgid "<guibutton>Screen Brightness</guibutton>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:275
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can control screen brightness through this keyword. In this form, some "
"&krunner; matches that let you do some common actions will be shown. If you "
"enter a value after the keyword (&eg;: <userinput>Screen Brightness "
"50</userinput>), the brightness will be set to that value."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: guibutton
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suspend"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
